			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This is, without a doubt, the BEST pling tool in the game.  I've gone around soloing decent mobs (lets say DW Crocs in oasis) for a few of my low level friends (8ish - 12is).  While they beat on something else with my buffs on them I'm rooting 3 - 5 crocs, nuking 'em down to a pixel, then atoning them.  After atoned, my little buddies run up, whack 'em, and get all the exp.<BR>
<BR>
There is a 100% chance the person will get the exp from an atoned mob, you just have to make sure YOU and all other 'high levels' are OFF it's hatelist.  How?, you ask?..usually the mob will turn in a different direction or just simply walk off when atoned...recently today my group was mobbed while I (the cleric) had to go to the bathroom..when i came back i simply celestial healed everyone and pulled some of the excess mobs away from the group, rooted them, and atoned them...1 of them was still aggroed cuz he was turning around in circles facing me..
				</font>
			</td>

