			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I apologize for my misinformation. Seems I was doing something wrong. Here is the gist of it as i see it. Atone is a mem blur spell. However what had confused me was when i was PL'ing a friend and used that spell it gave me the xp anyways, and here is how i figure it happened. After helping get the creature to 1/4 bub, I rooted it, then casted atone. But i made the mistake of healing my friend. Seems if you do something again to it, it does remember the xp list. Well after healing my friend i got the xp even tho i didnt do any damage to it. So if you arepl'ing a frined do not do anything, dont cast dont hit it nothing. However it is great for escaping the trains. just root the ones you dont want to fight have the people who are fighting the one pull it far enough out of aggro range then atone it. After the root's wear off just watch them walk away.<BR>
<BR>
Again my apologies for any misinformation I may have given.<BR>
<BR>
Lyndaya Soulmender<BR>
